Day 11 - Well would you look at that, even if not by a long shot, we've passed the 1/3 point of the month! Just 3 more days and we'll achieve the silver reward.

Remember that if you're ever feeling the urge, that's just an indication that you don't have anything better to do. Find a hobby you like, a video game you wanna play, a show you wanna watch, literally anything! This is the time of month where you'll have the most free time, and when you'll need things to do the most. Don't look at NNN as a challenge, look at it as an opportunity!

Here's a question to all of you: How has NNN improved you as a person? Have you been working out more? Maybe you have more motivation to delve deeper into your hobbies? I'd be interested in hearing about it. As a side note, thanks for all the support on these comments, it means a lot to me and I love hearing & upvoting all of your responses! <3

After the dine we set sail on Fallen Angel once again into the deep, dark zee. Instead of heading back to Fallen London I decided to head north instead, much to the crew's dismay. For few travelled up north, and those who do rarely return.

Not even a minute of sailing and the fog starts to roll around, the gunner struggling to see. "Storm's curse!" The Irrepressible Cannoneer shouts. "Misfortune is upon us!" I scoff at the statement.

Then, I heard a roar.

As the colossal purple mountain came into view, I know that I have made a mistake sailing here. Mt. Nomad, the niece of The Fathomking, had spotted us, and is looking for blood. I ring the bell, its toll echoing throughout the ship and out into the Zee. "All hands on deck!" I order with desperation, for we're no match to fight such ancient creature. The crew runs around the deck, helping to get us out of here. "Stoke the engine! Fuel the fire! Quickly!" I turn the wheel as the ship jets forward with a burst of power.
